column5: Would you put this in your front yard???  Or would your significant other let you??  That mailbox for me just wouldn't work.  Lol
Stop taking pictures of my house...
AHHHH YES!!! The extremely rare albino bass!!!

No way, that thing can hold too many past due notices. I guess you guys have never been in my rural neighborhood, the best one I like is the full size Stork with it's mouth open. Some would be considered folk art and would go for a few hun in a gallery in T.O.

I had the catfish version for 5 years. Then someone came along one weekend, while we were away, and stole the thing. Would have taken them a good 20 minutes to unbolt the thing from the steel railings. I'd get another, except that they will soon be cancelling local mail delivery
Was thinking of getting one when I bought my house last year, but with Canada Post cutting down on residential delivery I would sell it while you can still get cash for it.

Was thinking of getting one when I bought my house last year, but with Canada Post cutting down on residential delivery I would sell it while you can still get cash for it.  Don't worry and put one up; junk mail delivery will last for ever.  Dan.
That's true.  Junk mail will last forever lol.

turns out I just moved to the right place:)  im about to head out this morning and a van pulls up. guy get out and says would you like to pay for our newspaper?  i say thanks but no thanks(paper is like 10 pages about farming a couple times per week)  ok he says have a nice day sir, and removes the mailbox and off he goes!  hahahahah  its a rental place so the mailbox wasnt mine to begin with
